tion and trafficking awareness. Documented social justice commitment aligned with gender equality.", "source_query": "women''s discipleship programs Christian gender justice ministry", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Dorcas Medical Mission", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "dorcasmedical.org", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Religious-based international nonprofit providing medical, surgical, dental, and vision care to poor and underserved globally. Multi-specialty medical missions model.", "fit_score": 8, "fit_reason": "Established international medical missions ministry with multi-specialty approach. Global reach targeting underserved populations, clear healthcare mission focus.", "source_query": "faith-based medical missions organizations fundraising", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "e3 Partners - Deaf Church Planting", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "e3partners.org", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Mission organization conducting deaf church planting work internationally. Successfully launched new church for deaf in Tanzania, Africa through mission teams. Combines evangelistic outreach with church establishment for deaf communities. Part of broader church planting and discipleship mission.", "fit_score": 8, "fit_reason": "Documented deaf church planting results (Tanzania initiative), established mission organization with international reach, combines evangelism with disability-focused church establishment, clear giving infrastructure through mission organization.", "source_query": "deaf church planting ministry Christian organization accessibility", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Earth Ministry", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "earthministry.org", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Founded 1992 to connect Christian faith with environmental sustainability. Based in Seattle, mobilizes faith communities for environmental justice, sustainable policy advocacy, and institutional church greening through education and training.", "fit_score": 8, "fit_reason": "Explicitly Christian ministry rooted in Episcopal tradition; concrete environmental justice focus; established Seattle-area donor base; institutional church partnerships", "source_query": "Earth Ministry Christian creation care Seattle donations giving", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Easy Peasy All-in-One Homeschool", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "allinonehomeschool.com", "city": "Multiple", "state": "US", "summary": "Free, comprehensive online Christian homeschool curriculum created by Lee Giles, a missionary family mom. Curriculum entirely donation-sustained and supports struggling families locally and globally.", "fit_score": 8, "fit_reason": "Explicitly sustained by donations; founder Lee Giles active in missions (Bible translation project, international preaching); organized fundraising model", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Edify", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "www.edify.org", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Founded 2009, provides microfinance loans to Christ-centered schools in Africa and Latin America, offering training and education technology. 98% repayment rate. Serves 2,375+ schools in 16 countries. Co-founder: Chris Crane.", "fit_score": 8, "fit_reason": "Faith-based microfinance with explicit Christian school focus, documented lending programs, and public leadership", "source_query": "Edify Christian school microfinance loans organization", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Ekemini Uwan Ministry", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "ekeminispeaks.com", "city": "Virginia", "state": "VA", "summary": "Independent Christian speaker and antiracism educator with speaking ministry, personal prayer letters, and support platform for racial justice teaching", "fit_score": 8, "fit_reason": "Individual leader with prayer letter circulation, speaking tour fundraising, and personal giving platform", "source_query": "Wave 2 Hunter Research", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Engaging Disability", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "engagingdisability.org", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Gospel-centered disability ministry coaching churches to disciple every member. Trains leaders, coaches congregations, and provides adapted discipleship resources for disability inclusion. Focus on theological foundations of disability inclusion and practical church implementation.", "fit_score": 8, "fit_reason": "Specialized coaching and training model for churches with theological grounding, documented resource development, clear target audience (church leaders), trained facilitator network, addresses discipleship accessibility gap, established web presence.", "source_query": "Engaging Disability gospel centered ministry", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}, {"org_name": "Episcopal Church - Social Justice & Advocacy Engagement", "org_type": "ministry", "website": "www.episcopalchurch.org/ministries/social-justice-advocacy-engagement", "city": null, "state": null, "summary": "Episcopal Church''s comprehensive social justice initiative connecting people from pews to public square. Partners with Poor People''s Campaign in advocating for truth-telling and social change within racism, poverty, ecological devastation, and war economy systems.", "fit_score": 8, "fit_reason": "Major Christian denomination with documented social justice infrastructure, national reach, partnership with Poor People''s Campaign. Established institutional funding and donor networks through Episcopal Church structure.", "source_query": "denominational social justice networks initiatives Christian churches", "meta": {"import_source": "FINAL_CONSOLIDATED_ALL_WAVES.json"}}]'::jsonb)
  as x(org_name text, org_type text, website text, city text, state text,
       summary text, fit_score int, fit_reason text, source_query text, meta jsonb)),
-- Count how many existing rows (queue + pipeline) share each URL.
-- A URL on exactly one row is a person-specific page safe to dedup
-- against; a URL shared by many is a roster/platform page and must
-- NOT cause a skip, or we'd drop distinct people who list it.
existing_sites as (
  select site, count(*) as n from (
    select rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/') as site
      from sales.scout_candidates where website is not null and btrim(website) <> ''
    union all
    select rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/') as site
      from sales.leads where website is not null and btrim(website) <> ''
  ) w group by site)
insert into sales.scout_candidates
  (org_name, org_type, website, city, state, summary,
   fit_score, fit_reason, source_query, status, meta)
select s.org_name, s.org_type, s.website, s.city, s.state, s.summary,
       s.fit_score, s.fit_reason, s.source_query, 'pending', coalesce(s.meta, '{}'::jsonb)
from src s
where not exists (select 1 from sales.scout_candidates c
                  where lower(trim(c.org_name)) = lower(trim(s.org_name)))
  and not exists (select 1 from sales.leads l
                  where lower(trim(l.org_name)) = lower(trim(s.org_name)))
  and not exists (select 1 from existing_sites es
                  where s.website is not null and btrim(s.website) <> ''
                    and es.n = 1
                    and es.site = rtrim(lower(regexp_replace(s.website, '^https?://(www\.)?', '', 'i')), '/'));